abstract: Cisco Systems, the largest maker of networking equipment, reported that its net income in the fourth quarter rose 4.4 percent, to $2 billion, from a year ago.
snippet: Cisco Systems, the largest maker of networking equipment, reported that its net income in the fourth quarter rose 4.4 percent, to $2 billion, from a year ago.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Cisco Systems posted strong earnings on Tuesday, pleasing investors who had feared that its sales would take a hit in a slowing economy.

headline.print_headline: Cisco Beats Expectations As Earnings Rise 4.4%
